title: Static Analysis

android.permission.EXPAND_STATUS_BAR.description: Allows application to expand or collapse the status bar.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.READ_SMS.description: Allows application to read SMS messages stored on your phone or SIM card. Malicious applications may read your confidential messages.

android.permission.WRITE_SMS.description: Allows application to write to SMS messages stored on your phone or SIM card. Malicious applications may delete your messages.

android.permission.RECEIVE_SMS.description: Allows application to receive and process SMS messages. Malicious applications may monitor your messages or delete them without showing them to you.

android.permission.RECEIVE_MMS.description: Allows application to receive and process MMS messages. Malicious applications may monitor your messages or delete them without showing them to you.

android.permission.RECEIVE_WAP_PUSH.description: Allows application to receive and process WAP messages. Malicious applications may monitor your messages or delete them without showing them to you.

android.permission.SEND_SMS.description: Allows application to send SMS messages. Malicious applications may cost you money by sending messages without your confirmation.

android.permission.READ_CONTACTS.description: Allows an application to read all of the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your data to other people.

android.permission.WRITE_CONTACTS.description: Allows an application to modify the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to erase or modify your contact data.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.GET_TASKS.description: Allows application to retrieve information about currently and recently running tasks. May allow malicious applications to discover private information about other applications.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to connect to and disconnect from Wi-Fi access points and to make changes to configured Wi-Fi networks.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows an application to view configuration of the local Bluetooth phone and to make and accept connections with paired devices.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.CHANGE_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to change the state of network connectivity.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to the SD card.

android.permission.CALL_PHONE.description: Allows the application to call phone numbers without your intervention. Malicious applications may cause unexpected calls on your phone bill. Note that this does not allow the application to call emergency numbers.

android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO.description: Allows application to access the audio record path.

android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW.description: Allows an application to show system-alert windows. Malicious applications can take over the entire screen of the phone.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.DISABLE_KEYGUARD.description: Allows an application to disable the key lock and any associated password security. A legitimate example of this is the phone disabling the key lock when receiving an incoming phone call, then re-enabling the key lock when the call is finished.

android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS.description: Allows an application to access the list of accounts known by the phone.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

com.android.launcher.permission.WRITE_SE.description: Allows an application to modify the system's settings data. Malicious applications can corrupt your system's configuration.

com.htc.launcher.permission.WRITE_SETTIN.description: Allows an application to modify the system's settings data. Malicious applications can corrupt your system's configuration.

com.huawei.android.launcher.permission.W.description: Allows an application to modify the system's settings data. Malicious applications can corrupt your system's configuration.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

manifest_analysis.title:
App has a Network Security Configuration
[android:networkSecurityConfig]
manifest_analysis.desc: The Network Security Configuration feature lets apps customize their network security settings in a safe, declarative configuration file without modifying app code. These settings can be configured for specific domains and for a specific app.
manifest_analysis.name: App has a Network Security Configuration [android:networkSecurityConfig]

manifest_analysis.title:
Application Data can be Backed up
[android:allowBackup=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: This flag allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.
manifest_analysis.name: Application Data can be Backed up [android:allowBackup=true]

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.mplus.lib.ui.main.MainActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

strings: "ad_consent_dialog_body1" : "You have chosen to use Textra for FREE. In return targeted ads will be shown from our ad partners."
"ad_consent_dialog_body2" : "We value your privacy, and so are letting you know these ad partners may use your phone's AAID (Android Advertising ID) and IP address to show you more relevant ads."
"ad_consent_dialog_body3" : "Alternatively, you can Upgrade to Pro, which is ad free."
"ad_consent_dialog_body4" : "Please refer to Settings > About > Privacy Policy for more information, including our ad partners, opting out of targeted ads and your right to be forgotten."
"allow_overlay" : "To use this feature, please enable the 'Draw / Display over other apps' permission (also known as 'Apps that can appear on top') for Textra."

"allow_overlay2" : "It's considered by Android to be a special permission, so on most phones you access it from the gear or dot-dot-dot icon (top right) in Android Settings > Apps, and not from the Textra permissions screen."
"allow_overlay3" : "Can't find the setting? An uninstall and fresh install fixes the missing permission."
"android_auto_disable_sms_permission_dialog_blurb" : "To avoid duplicate notifications, you need to turn off the SMS permission in the Android Auto app settings."
"android_auto_enable_summary" : "When turned on, messages that have been read to you will be marked as read, and delivery receipts and blacklisting will work."
"app_icon_changed_body" : "Your app icon has changed! So, you need to add it back to your home screen again."
"billing_error" : "An error occurred with Google Billing (error code %1$d)"
"blacklist_empty" : "To blacklist, long press in the conversation list and select "Blacklist" from the menu."
"blacklist_empty2" : "When blacklisted contacts send you messages they are hidden and you don't get notified about them."
"bot_help9_toUser_offer" : "You can get help by going to Settings > Support. You can find answers there, or ask a human. Do you want me to take you there (type 'yes')?"
"bot_huawei_close_apps_note" : "Important: to make sure Textra functions properly, go to Android Settings > Battery > 'Close apps after screen lock' and turn the Textra entry OFF"
"bot_im_simple" : "Sorry, I'm just a simple bot! You can type '%1$s' to get a tip."
"bot_im_simple2" : "Welcome to Textra. I'm a simple bot. You can send me anything you want, but I only understand some simple things. For example, you can type '%1$s' to get a tip."
"bot_mms_audio_toUser" : "Are you trying to tell me something?"
"bot_mms_vcard_toUser" : "Thanks, I'll update my little black book"
"bot_tip10_toUser" : "Tip: you can lock messages so you can't accidentally delete them. Lock messages by long pressing them and choosing '%1$s' in the dot-dot-dot menu."
"bot_tip1_toUser" : "Tip: on the right hand side of the screen there are hidden timestamps for each bubble. Drag a bubble to the left to see them. Try it now!"
"bot_tip2_toUser" : "Tip: tap on a bubble to get quick options. Try it now! Then tap '%1$s'."
"bot_tip3_toUser" : "Tip: in the conversation list, drag left to reveal the call icon. Drag right for delete icon and message count."
"bot_tip6_toUser" : "Tip: tap the + icon, then long press the images icon to quickly select your most recent picture."
"bot_tip7_toUser" : "Tip: in the + panel, long press the camera icon to launch the full camera app."
"bot_tip8_toUser" : "Tip: in the + panel, tap the gallery icon, then long press any picture to make it larger."
"bot_tip9_toUser" : "Tip: tap the + icon to add things to a message. Try it now!"
"common_google_play_services_enable_text" : "%1$s won't work unless you enable Google Play services."

playstore_details.title: Textra SMS
playstore_details.description:
Want a beautiful, super fast and highly customizable alternative to your stock Android messaging app?

Well today is your day. Textra is simply outstanding!

Comes with a bunch of great features, notably 180+ material design theme, bubble & app icon colors. Dark, light & auto-night modes, multiple bubble styles, scheduled (future) SMS & MMS, stop during send, slide to delete, slide to call, quick snap camera, multi-select picture gallery, quick reply SMS popup, awesome MMS GROUP messaging, quick voice memos, GIFs, 21 text sizes, message blocker / blacklisting, pin-to-top, automatic video & picture compression, plus heaps more!

Customize your preferred theme & bubble colors, signatures and notifications (icon shape, LED color, sound, vibration, privacy, reminders and muting) PER CONTACT as well.

Get all the latest (2900+) Android, Twitter, Emoji One & iOS style emojis including diversity (skin tone). Just pick your preferred emoji style and express yourself!

NEW: Copy Partial Text inside a bubble, tap a bubble to check out this great new feature!

It's pretty special; try it, tell your friends, shout from the treetops, but most of all enjoy it.

Fully compatible with Pushbullet, MightyText, Android Wear and Android Auto (car) for enhanced notifications and quick reply.

All Textra features are free forever. Occasionally you'll see an ad, or you can choose to make a once only in-app purchase to remove ads forever.

Support, Knowledge Base & Feedback @ https://textra.uservoice.com

Simple. Beautiful. Fast.
